 Control Statements – Theory

Control statements determine the flow of execution in a program.

Types of Control Statements
1. Selection (Decision-Making) Statements

Used to choose between alternatives.

if
if-else
else-if ladder
nested if
switch-case (C, C++, Java)

Example:

if (x > 0)
{
    printf("Positive");
}
else
{
    printf("Negative");
}

2. Iteration (Looping) Statements

Used to execute a block repeatedly.

for
while
do-while

Example:

for(int i=1; i<=5; i++)
{
    printf("%d ", i);
}

3. Jump Statements

Used to transfer control from one part of a program to another.

break
continue
goto
return

Example:

for(int i=1; i<=10; i++)
{
    if(i==5)
        break;
}
